  "pages": [
    {
      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "The city council was ready last\nnight to pass the ordinance for paw\ning Brownies addition with asphalt\nfrom the river to Fourth avenue,\nMonroe street to Hangman creek,\nbut the question of whether it was\nlegal to advertise the job for let\nting \"as whole or in part\" must\nfirst be settled. The idea of\n\n\nawarding the job in sections was\nconceived to favor small contrac-\ntors that might want to bid on it.\nThe matter was referred to the\nboard of works, to be guided by the\nopinion of the corporation counsel."
    }
